<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-01-30T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-01-30T02:00:00-05:00" n="846" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d846">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.6363/60: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-01-30T15:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">January 30,
                                        1926—3 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received January 30—5:42
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>59. American consul at Swatow telegraphs that Swatow authorities have
                            instituted oil monopoly similar to that in operation at Canton—see
                            Canton’s despatch 366, October 27th, to Department.<note n="92" xml:id="d846fn92">Not printed.</note></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>